Vice President Mike Pence met with President of Serbia Aleksandar Vučić to discuss the importance of the bilateral relationship and the desire to deepen the partnership between the United States and Serbia. Pence expressed U.S. support for Serbia's efforts to join the European Union and the need for continued reforms. The leaders also discussed the Vice President's upcoming trip to Podgorica, Montenegro, where he will participate in an Adriatic Charter Summit with leaders from the Western Balkans region. Pence announced that the United States will provide an additional $10 million contribution to the Regional Housing Program, which helps provide housing to those displaced during the conflicts in the former Yugoslavia in the 1990s.